  "market_context": "Uptrend confirmed on daily and 1H charts; price broke above key resistance. Analyst zoomed into 5min after CHoCH signal to trade pullbacks into order blocks toward prior high target.",
  "key_observation": "Price formed multiple consecutive order blocks during an upward move; the analyst opened long positions at each OB with reduced risk, accepting that some stops may be hit before reaching the final target.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Confirmed higher-timeframe bullish structure on daily chart (break above resistance) and 1H smooth uptrend, aligning bias to long only.",
    "Step 2: Identified CHoCH on 5min chart as reversal signal after downtrend, signaling short-term bearish exhaustion.",
    "Step 3: Waited for price to form first order block on 5min, entered long position with stop below the OB zone.",
    "Step 4: As price rose, a second order block formed; opened another long without closing the first, using reduced risk per trade.",
    "Step 5: Price hit stop of second trade (and triggered first), yet analyst opened a third long at a newly formed OB, continuing until reaching target at prior high.",
    "Step 6: Emphasized risk management: ≤2% risk per trade, max three active trades, and adherence to rules despite losing trades."
  ],
  "outcome": "Second trade stopped out; first trade likely also stopped; third trade reached target at prior high — overall strategy profitable after backtesting.",
  "lessons": "In strong trends, multiple order blocks can form sequentially; trading them with scaled risk improves win rate and R:R. Accepting partial losses is part of the process when targeting major HTF levels.",
